        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 26 at 5:01PM PDT by NWS Portland OR</headline>
        <description>At 501 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Cougar, moving north at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Johnston Ridge Visitors Center, Coldwater Ridge Visitors Center,
Coldwater Lake, and Cougar.

In Washington this includes State Route 504 between mile markers 26
and 51.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM PDT for
southwestern Washington.</instruction>
